{
  "texts": [
    "For CT images, we initially normalized the Hounsfield units using typical window width and level values.",
    "The employed window width and level values for soft tissues, lung, and brain are (W:400, L:40), (W:1500, L:-160), and (W:80, L:40), respectively.",
    "Subsequently, the intensity values were rescaled to the range of [0, 255].",
    "For MR, X-ray, ultrasound, mammography, and optical coherence tomography (OCT) images, we clipped the intensity values to the range between the 0.5th and 99.5th percentiles before rescaling them to the range of [0, 255].",
    "Regarding RGB images (e.g., endoscopy, dermoscopy, fundus, and pathology images), if they were already within the expected intensity range of [0, 255], their intensities remained unchanged."
  ]
}